Irish Apple and Parsnip Soup
  --Sur la Table

4 oz unsalted butter
1 large shallot, minced
1 leek (white part only), halved lengthwise, washed and dried, cut into 1/4" pieces
1 clove garlic, crushed
1 large (3/4 lb) Yukon Gold potato, peeled and cut into 1" pieces
2 parsnips (~1/2 lb), peeled and cut into 1" pieces
2 Granny Smith apples, peeled, cored and chopped into 2" pieces
5 c vegetable broth
2 c apple juice
1 c whole milk
1/2 c flat leaf parsley
Kosher salt and freshly black pepper

Place a large saucepan on the stove over a medium heat. Add the butter, and when melted, add shallots, leeks and garlic and using a wooden spoon to occasionally stir. Cook until leeks are tender, ~7 min. Add the potato, parsnips and apples and cook until just potatoes are starting to soften, ~5 min. Add the broth and apple juice; reduce stove temperature to a simmer. Cover the saucepan and cook until the vegetables are very soft, ~30 min. Remove the saucepan from the heat, add the parsley and using a blender, or an immersion blender, thoroughly purée the mixture. Return the saucepan to the stove over a medium-low heat and stir in the milk. Heat the soup, stirring occasionally, until the soup is heated through and boils. Taste and season with salt and pepper.
